column2: Mumbai Indians (abbreviated as MI) is a franchise cricket team representing the city of Mumbai, Maharashtra, in the Indian Premier League (IPL).
An arsenal is a place where arms and ammunition are made, maintained and repaired, stored, or issued, in any combination, whether privately or publicly owned.
The Australian Hockey League (AHL)  is Australia’s premier national domestic field hockey competition.

Human overpopulation (or population overshoot) occurs when the ecological footprint of a human population in a specific geographical location exceeds the carrying capacity of the place occupied by that group.

The Spain national football team (Spanish: Selección de fútbol de España) represents Spain in men's International association football and is controlled by the Royal Spanish Football Federation, the governing body for football in Spain.
Team Sky (UCI team code: SKY) is a British professional cycling team that competes in the UCI World Tour.
The Cycling Federation of India is the national governing body of cycle racing in India.

Road bicycle racing is the cycle sport discipline of road cycling, held on paved roads.
